The paper discusses a security mechanism for monitoring packet trajectories in computer networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The mechanism is based on software-defined networking (SDN) technology, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for detecting adversarial behavior, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and performance evaluation of the proposed mechanism, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
